This paper deals with online learning algorithms, which are commonly studied in the machine learning community. The focus on regret minimization and the proposed algorithms suggest that this paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance measures of dynamic regret and adaptive regret, which are relevant to the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT). The algorithms proposed in the paper also involve optimization and decision-making, which are relevant to the fields of data structures (cs.DS) and control systems (cs.SY).
